label.value: Contagion Contact

value.value: Any exposure to a suspected or confirmed infectious agent.

label.value: Physical Contagion Contact

value.value: Exposure from touching an object, person, or body substance contaminated with a suspected or confirmed infectious agent.

label.value: Respiratory Contagion Contact

value.value: Exposure to a suspected or confirmed infectious agent via air droplets.

label.value: Metastatic Fibrosarcoma

value.value: Fibrosarcoma that has spread from its original site of growth to another anatomic site.

label.value: Stage 0 Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IA Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1, N0, M0.  T1: Tumor 5 mm or less in greatest dimension.  No invasion of the tarsal plate or eyelid margin.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IB Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IB includes: T2a, N0, M0.  T2a: Tumor more than 5 mm, but not more than 10 mm in greatest dimension.  Or, any tumor that invades the tarsal plate or eyelid margin.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: WHO Mycobacterium Quantitation Scheme

value.value: A scale, endorsed by the World Health Organization, for reporting the quantitation of Mycobacterium present in a sputum sample.

label.value: Scanty Score

value.value: A finding of 1-9 acid-fast bacilli per 100 immersion fields.

label.value: Stage IC Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IC includes: T2b, N0, M0.  T2b: Tumor more than 10 mm, but not more than 20 mm in greatest dimension.  Or, tumor involves full thickness of the eyelid.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: 1+ Score, WHO

value.value: A finding of 10-99 acid-fast bacilli per 100 immersion fields.

label.value: Stage II Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: T3a, N0, M0.  T3a: Tumor more than 20 mm in greatest dimension.  Or, any tumor that invades adjacent ocular or orbital structures.  Or, any T with perineural tumor invasion.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: 2+ Score, WHO

value.value: A finding of 1-10 acid-fast bacilli per 1 immersion field.

label.value: Stage IIIA Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: T3b, N0, M0.  T3b: Complete tumor resection requires enucleation, exenteration, or bone resection.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Metastatic Leiomyosarcoma

value.value: A leiomyosarcoma that has spread to other anatomic sites.

label.value: 3+ Score, WHO

value.value: A finding of greater than 10 acid-fast bacilli per 1 immersion field.

label.value: Stage IIIB Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: Any T, N1, M0.  N1: Regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIC Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIC includes: T4, Any N, M0.  T4: Tumor is not resectable due to extensive invasion of ocular, orbital, craniofacial structures, or brain.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Eyelid Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: Any T, Any N, M1.  M1: Distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Steroid Myopathy

value.value: A non-neoplastic disorder affecting the skeletal muscles. It is caused by damage to muscle fibers either by excessive intake of corticosteroids (steroid treatment) or high levels of endogenous corticosteroids due to hormonal abnormalities. Patients usually present with weakness mainly in the proximal muscles of the upper and lower extremities and the neck flexors.

label.value: Stage IIA Uveal Melanoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIA includes: (T1b-d, N0, M0); (T2a, N0, M0). T1b: Iris: Tumor limited to the iris more than 3 clock hours in size.  Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 1 with ciliary body involvement.  T1c: Iris: Tumor limited to the iris with secondary glaucoma.  Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 1 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter.  T1d: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 1 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter. T2a: Iris: Tumor confluent with or extending into the ciliary body, choroid, or both, with secondary glaucoma.  Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 2 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIB Uveal Melanoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIB includes: (T2b, N0, M0); (T3a, N0, M0).  T2b: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 2 with ciliary body involvement.  T3a: Iris: Tumor confluent with or extending into the ciliary body, choroid, or both, with sclera extension and secondary glaucoma. Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 3 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Uveal Melanoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: (T2c-d, N0, M0); (T3b-c, N0, M0); (T4a, N0, M0).  T2c: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 2 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter. T2d: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 2 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter. T3b: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 3 with ciliary body involvement. T3c: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 3 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter. T4a: Iris: Tumor with extrascleral extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter.  Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 4 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Uveal Melanoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: (T3d, N0, M0); (T4b-c, N0, M0).  T3d: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 3 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter.  T4b: Iris: Tumor with extrascleral extension more than 5 mm in diameter.  Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 4 with ciliary body involvement.  T4c: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 4 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIC Uveal Melanoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIC includes: T4d-e, N0, M0.  T4d: Ciliary body and choroid: Tumor size category 4 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in diameter.  T4e: Ciliary body and choroid: Any tumor size category with extraocular extension more than 5 mm in diameter.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Localized Leiomyosarcoma

value.value: Leiomyosarcoma that is confined to a specific site without evidence of spread to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Paced Rhythm

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in which the cardiac rhythm is controlled by an electrical impulse from an artificial cardiac pacemaker. (CDISC)

label.value: Obturator Lymph Node

value.value: A pelvic lymph node located along the obturator artery.

label.value: Internal Iliac Lymph Node

value.value: A lymph node located along the internal iliac artery.

label.value: External Iliac Lymph Node

value.value: A lymph node located along the external iliac artery.

label.value: Mosaic

value.value: An individual containing two or more populations of genetically different cells that arose from a single zygote.

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: A non-Hodgkin lymphoma arising from the conjunctiva, lacrimal gland, lacrimal drainage apparatus, eyelids, or other orbital tissues around the eye.  The vast majority of cases are extranodal marginal zone lymphomas of mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue, however, other histologic types of lymphomas can originate from ocular adnexal tissues, including rare cases of NK/T-cell lymphomas of nasal type.

label.value: Unprotected Sexual Intercourse

value.value: Sexual intercourse without the use of precautions to prevent conception or the transmission of sexually transmitted diseases.

label.value: Cerebellar Peduncle

value.value: One of three pairs of nerve fiber bundles that originate from the cerebellum and link it to the brainstem.

label.value: Milligram per Square Meter per Week

value.value: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s) per square meter per period of time equal to seven days.

label.value: Meaning

value.value: The idea or message that is intended, expressed, or signified.

label.value: Recurrent Leiomyosarcoma

value.value: The reemergence of leiomyosarcoma after a period of remission

label.value: Stage I Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage I includes: IA (T1, N0, M0, B0-1); IB (T2, N0, M0, B0-1). T1: Limited patches, papules, and/or plaques covering less than 10% of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T1a (patch only) vs. T1b (plaque +/- patch).  T2: Patches, papules, or plaques covering 10% or more of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T2a (patch only) vs. T2b (plaque +/- patch).  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IA Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1, N0, M0, B0-1.  T1: Limited patches, papules, and/or plaques covering less than 10% of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T1a (patch only) vs. T1b (plaque +/- patch).  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IB Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IB includes: T2, N0, M0, B0-1. T2: Patches, papules, or plaques covering 10% or more of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T2a (patch only) vs. T2b (plaque +/- patch).  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA (T1-2, N1-2, M0, B0-1); IIB (T3, N0-2, M0, B0-1). T1: Limited patches, papules, and/or plaques covering less than 10% of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T1a (patch only) vs. T1b (plaque +/- patch).  T2: Patches, papules, or plaques covering 10% or more of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T2a (patch only) vs. T2b (plaque +/- patch).  T3: One or more tumors (equal or greater than 1 cm diameter).  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIA Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIA includes: T1-2, N1-2, M0, B0-1.  T1: Limited patches, papules, and/or plaques covering less than 10% of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T1a (patch only) vs. T1b (plaque +/- patch).  T2: Patches, papules, or plaques covering 10% or more of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T2a (patch only) vs. T2b (plaque +/- patch).  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIB Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIB includes: T3, N0-2, M0, B0-1.  T3: One or more tumors (equal or greater than 1 cm diameter).  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Leukemia Cutis

value.value: Cutaneous involvement by an acute or chronic leukemia.

label.value: Stage III Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: (T4, N0-2, M0, B0-1); IIIA (T4, N0-2, M0, B0); IIIB (T4, N0-2, M0, B1). T4: Confluence of erythema covering 80% or more of body surface area.  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: T4, N0-2, M0, B0.  T4: Confluence of erythema covering 80% or more of body surface area.  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: T4, N0-2, M0, B1. T4: Confluence of erythema covering 80% or more of body surface area.  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Metastatic Liposarcoma

value.value: A liposarcoma that has metastasized to a secondary site.

label.value: Stage IV Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA1 (T1-4, N0-2, M0, B2); IVA2 (T1-4, N3, M0, B0-2); IVB (T1-4, N0-3, M1, B0-2). T1: Limited patches, papules, and/or plaques covering less than 10% of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T1a (patch only) vs. T1b (plaque +/- patch).  T2: Patches, papules, or plaques covering 10% or more of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T2a (patch only) vs. T2b (plaque +/- patch).  T3: One or more tumors (equal or greater than 1 cm diameter).  T4: Confluence of erythema covering 80% or more of body surface area.  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  N3: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grades 3-4 or NCI LN4; clone positive or negative.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  M1: Visceral involvement (must have pathology confirmation and organ involved should be specified).  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  B2: High blood tumor burden: 1000/microL Sezary cells or more with positive clone.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVA Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVA includes: IVA1 (T1-4, N0-2, M0, B2); IVA2 (T1-4, N3, M0, B0-2). T1: Limited patches, papules, and/or plaques covering less than 10% of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T1a (patch only) vs. T1b (plaque +/- patch).  T2: Patches, papules, or plaques covering 10% or more of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T2a (patch only) vs. T2b (plaque +/- patch).  T3: One or more tumors (equal or greater than 1 cm diameter).  T4: Confluence of erythema covering 80% or more of body surface area.  N0: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  N1: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  N2: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  N3: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grades 3-4 or NCI LN4; clone positive or negative.  M0: No visceral organ involvement.  B0: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  B1: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells) but does not meet the criteria of B2.  B2: High blood tumor burden: 1000/microL Sezary cells or more with positive clone.  (AJCC 7th ed.)
